nonattribution, Dastar killed us

00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:14.100
on one whole good
creative set of arguments.

00:16:14.100 --> 00:16:17.040
But one of the other problems
you have is the preemption.

00:16:17.040 --> 00:16:19.950
Like when I try to file,
or if I'm the defendant --

00:16:19.950 --> 00:16:24.120
I'm like 12(b)(6) -- when people
try to use unfair competition

00:16:24.120 --> 00:16:27.800
or other kinds of things, I
say, "Hey, it's preempted" or,

00:16:27.800 --> 00:16:30.770
you know, it's a problem I
have if I want to plead it

00:16:30.770 --> 00:16:34.430
because this is all subject
of the Copyright Act,

00:16:34.430 --> 00:16:35.990
and it is not included.

00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:39.010
So, the various different
kind of creative elements

00:16:39.010 --> 00:16:43.420
or arguments that one might
make I'm not real sure that,

00:16:43.420 --> 00:16:46.930
because of the preemption,
that they would get very far.

00:16:46.930 --> 00:16:50.540
So, just a practical
thing there.

00:16:56.320 --> 00:16:58.710
&gt;&gt; Matthew Barblan:
